1. An identifier cannot be declared multiple times in the same scope.
2. An identifier must be declared before its use.
3. The types returned by a function must be the same as that of variable used to store the return value of the function.

4. Function input parameters passed while invoking it should be of the same
   type as those used in the function definition. Number of input parameters
   must be same as that of those used in the function definition.


5. Two functions declarations cannot have same name.

6. Function overLoading is not allowed.

7. The function cannot be invoked recursively.

8. An identifier used beyond its scope must be viewed as undefined

9. The right hand side expression of an assignment statement must be of the
same type as that of the left hand side identifier.

10. each program should have a main function.
